Etymology[edit]

From cōn- (“with”) +‎ foedus (“pact, agreement”) +‎ -ō (1st conjugation verbal suffix).

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /konˈfoe̯.de.roː/, [kõːˈfoe̯.d̪ɛ.ɾoː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /konˈfe.de.ro/, [kɔnˈfɛː.d̪ɛ.rɔ]

Verb[edit]

cōnfoederō (present infinitive cōnfoederāre, perfect active cōnfoederāvī, supine cōnfoederātum); first conjugation

  1. (chiefly Ecclesiastical Latin) to unite or join by a league
